{
  "stem": "95.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never heard of them anymore, those two-- two sisters.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Amazingly, when I went to Israel in 1981 for the gathering, one great niece from my-- from my older sister, Sarah, was there with-- with her children.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With her-- a niece and her children were there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They live-- they live in Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that-- they didn't tell me what happened to her mother, if she was deported or-- some people went, you know, to Russia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some-- I don't know if they got killed by-- by-- or sent to prison, or sent to camps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have no idea what happened to those two people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the first thing we had to do is to go and register to the police station to have a big J stamp on our ID cards.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Secondly is to have the Star of David put in the front of our-- front of our coat, pinned or sewn in the front of our coat, with the word [FRENCH], which means Jew.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Curfews.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Curfews. 8:00 PM to 8:00 AM, you cannot be seen on the streets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Cannot go to schools anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You cannot-- you cannot-- you cannot travel with anybody else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We have to have a special compartments in the metro and subways in Paris.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in the-- in the buses, we have to be in a-- just two seats only for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We cannot seat-- we cannot sit with anybody else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it's frightening.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, we are suddenly the plague.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We are the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we are not human beings.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, they just-- they look at us-- you know, if a German walks, we have to go off the-- off the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We have to-- we let them go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Otherwise, they're going to slap us.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
